      Agile Testing 
Agile Testing is most useful in dynamic, fast-changing environments where requirements evolve frequently and teams need to deliver high-quality software quickly and incrementally.
   Agile Testing is useful in industries such as:
1. Software Development: Agile Testing is widely used in software development.
2. E-commerce: Agile Testing helps e-commerce companies adapt to changing requirements.
3. Finance: Agile Testing enables financial institutions to deliver high-quality software quickly.
 Why Agile Testing?
1. Faster Time-To-Market: Deliver working software quickly.
2. Improved Quality: Focus on delivering high-quality software.
3. Flexibility: Adapt to changing requirements and priorities.
4. Collaboration: Emphasizes collaboration between team members and stakeholders.

